&lt;li&gt;Own production reliability for the APAC region — monitoring systems, triaging alerts, coordinating incident response, and serving as one of the key engineering references for merchants and partners operating across Southeast Asia;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Investigate and troubleshoot complex production issues across the stack, including integrations with payment partners such as PSPs, acquirers, and local payment rails;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the onboarding, go-live, and stabilization of new payment integrations and market expansions in APAC — participating in new market and product launches from integration all the way to production readiness;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement hotfixes for critical production issues and conduct root cause analyses to identify systemic risks and prevent recurrence;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve observability coverage for APAC services — building and tuning dashboards, alerts, and runbooks using tools like Datadog and OpenSearch so issues are detected before they impact merchants;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the operational foundations of the Singapore Engineering Hub: incident response playbooks, on-call processes, deployment standards, and ways of working;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and mitigate systemic risks in production — through code reviews, post-mortems, and proactive reliability improvements — to reduce incident frequency and revenue impact;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with EBANX&#39;s engineering teams in Brazil to ensure knowledge transfer, consistent practices, and alignment across time zones;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Our stack &amp;amp; work environment: MacOS, GitHub Enterprise, Datadog, OpenSearch, Claude, &lt;a href=&quot;http://Devin.ai&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Devin.ai&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
