&lt;p&gt;EBANX is one of the most successful fintechs to emerge from Latin America — and today, we are building a truly global payments company. Our mission has remained constant from day one: to unlock access and enable companies and consumers to participate in the digital economy, no matter where they are.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;What started as a bold vision has grown into a platform that connects some of the world’s largest digital businesses with customers across 21 of the fastest-growing markets. We operate where complexity exists — turning local challenges into global opportunities, and building the infrastructure that allows payments to move further, faster, and smarter.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are a team of builders and problem-solvers. We think globally, act with curiosity, and believe diversity of thought is a competitive advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As EBANX enters its next phase of hyper growth, we are looking for people who want to shape the future of payments, expand what’s possible, and help connect businesses and consumers across borders.&lt;br&gt;Let’s build what’s next — together.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At EBANX’s Product Performance team, you don’t just create features. You develop user-centered solutions that transform the experience of millions of consumers and global companies. Every product decision has a real impact on the future of digital payments, combining strategic vision, innovation, and collaboration to make our work truly &lt;strong&gt;Out Of The Ordinary&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Senior Product Analyst for Payments Performance, you will play a key role in ensuring the performance, reliability, and continuous evolution of our card products and payment platform. You will be responsible for identifying, analyzing, and implementing strategies to improve critical capabilities such as Network Token, Card-on-File, Account Updater, and 3DS, while maintaining operational excellence across multiple markets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working closely with Engineering, Operations, Commercial teams, and external partners, you will leverage data and analytical insights to optimize authorization rates, strengthen redundancy strategies across countries and providers, and drive discovery initiatives that unlock new opportunities to improve payment performance and merchant experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is ideal for someone who enjoys solving complex problems, working cross-functionally, and combining analytical thinking with product strategy to continuously enhance the performance and scalability of a global payments ecosystem.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What your day-to-day will look like&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and continuously improve card performance capabilities such as Network Token, Card-on-File, Account Updater, 3DS, and other products that impact authorization rates and merchant experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze payment performance metrics, identify trends and opportunities, and drive data-driven initiatives to improve conversion, reliability, and operational excellence across multiple markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Engineering, Operations, Commercial teams, and external partners to investigate issues, prioritize opportunities, and deliver solutions that enhance payment performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead discovery initiatives and evaluate new technologies, providers, and strategies to increase approval rates, strengthen redundancy between countries and partners, and expand our product capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and maintain monitoring frameworks, KPIs, and processes that ensure continuous optimization and scalability of the payments ecosystem.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay up to date with industry trends and payment technologies to ensure our products remain competitive and aligned with market best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
